SIMPLE: moratorium
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moratorium
<hw>Mor`a*to"ri*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Moratory</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A period
during which an obligor has a legal right to delay meeting an
obligation, esp. such a period granted, as to a bank, by a moratory
law.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a suspension of an activity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>an officially authorized period of delay or waiting;
<as>as, a <ex>moratorium</ex> on putting a law into
effect</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Moratory</ent>⟦br⟧
